setup fresh maptool install (tested 1.4, 1.7):



distances 1,2,1,2,...
menu > edit > preferences > interactions >
    Maps:
        Movement metric :  ONE_TWO_ONE
        New maps have Fog of War  :  check
        New maps visible to players  :  no
        New Map Light : DAY
    Chat:
        use tooltips for inline rolls  :  check



make tokens facing 45deg snap on shift+mousewheel
fine facing adjustments can be made by crtl+shift+mousewheel
maptool 1.4:
menu > edit > preferences:
bottom right:
	Facing: check both:
		On Edges     check
		On Vertices  check



menu > edit > campaign properties >
    Token Properties >
        import :  campaignproperties.mtprops       <<  remember to press "Update" and "OK"



Import GM quick button functions (global macros):
menu > Window >
    Global  :  check
in Global subwindow:
    right click > import macro set  :  global.mtmacset



library function (library token)
file: Lib_util.rptok    <<  name with "_" for windows compatibility, should be ":"
name: Lib:util       <<  CRUCIAL !!  the imported token must be named "Lib:util" in game
Must be added to ONLY ONE map in the campaign file.
I usually use a hidden map "! playground" for lib token, auto spawn tokens, effect templates, various general region tokens, etc



campaign functions (specific for each campaign)
got nothing here yet, usually use global for GM and token specific macros

